<s> The above example was just to show that a simple paren matching algorithm would not need any special case handling for their presence.  </s>
<s> Let me clarify my intent in the exercise.  </s>
<s> I wanted to see if one could, within today's 8879, 1) use a single character to terminate elements, and 2) enable the use of a simple character counting algorith to track your location in an XML document, and 3) solve Arjun Ray's problem with tag-soupers' spanning element tendency.  </s>
<s> It turns out that NET can be that single character, and if you use a sequence of two of its mate for STAGO, you have something that appears to meet the three criteria.  </s>
<s> As it happens, by defining a rule which say's TAGC is only used on end tags and start tags with EMPTY content, you have the flip-side of the trapeze act, and no need to alter 8879 to distinguish ETAGC and STAGC.  </s>
<s> Now, just to be a bit more radical, if we do decide that un-minimized end tags are more harmful than they're worth, and we decide it is not necessary to identify EMPTY elements, then we no longer have any use for either ETAGO or TAGC.  </s>
